         <div type="translation">
            <head>Translation</head>
            <ab>May the illustrious feet of Civappirakācaṉ thrive. Jovian year Caṟuvatāri, month of
               Māci, 29th day: the copy that was copied (eḻut°) by Cittampalavaṉ of Pātūr having
               checked the manuscript of the copy of Amuṟtapāṇi Tampirāṉ, who is in Pommapuri. The
               illustrious feet of Ñāṉatēcikaṉ are the support, may the teacher thrive, the teacher
               is the support; once there is the benevolent gaze of Civa (i.e. Śiva) [and] there is
               awakening of the intellect (ñāṉotaya) and compassion, one will (kaṭavatu) shine.
               There should graciously be the rising ground (tiṭṭai) of Ñāṉakuru. This [text] has
               been copied after its commentary.”</ab>
         </div>
